## Example of statement
['A jewelry-themed party sounds like a great idea! Your sister will surely love the thought and effort you\'ve put into creating a celebration that revolves around her current interests. Here are some more ideas to complement your plans:\n\n**Decorations:**\n\n* **Silver and white balloons:** As you mentioned, silver and white balloons will create a beautiful and elegant atmosphere. You could also add some clear balloons with glitter or confetti inside to give them a sparkly effect.\n* **Jewelry display:** Set up a display case or a table with some of your sister\'s favorite pieces of jewelry, or some costume jewelry that fits the silver and diamond theme. This will add a personal touch to the decor.\n* **Diamond-shaped decorations:** Use diamond-shaped decorations, such as paper cutouts or cardboard shapes, to add to the theme. You could hang them from the ceiling or place them on the walls.\n* **Glittering backdrops:** Create a glittering backdrop using silver or white fabric, or even a giant piece of cardboard covered in glitter. This will make for a great photo opportunity!\n\n**Jewelry Bar:**\n\n* **Fake jewelry:** As you mentioned, providing fake jewelry pieces, such as beads, chains, and pendants, will allow guests to create their own unique pieces. You could also include some jewelry-making tools, like wire cutters and pliers.\n* **Jewelry-making stations:** Set up separate stations with different materials, such as beads, charms, or rhinestones, to let guests create their own jewelry pieces.\n* **Jewelry boxes:** Provide small jewelry boxes or pouches for guests to store their creations in. This will make them feel like they\'re taking home a special treasure.\n\n**Food and Drinks:**\n\n* **Diamond-shaped treats:** Serve diamond-shaped cookies, cakes, or sandwiches to fit the theme. You could also have "gemstone"-colored drinks, such as blue or pink lemonade.\n* **"Jewel-toned" cocktails:** Create special cocktails with silver or diamond-inspired names, such as a "Silver Sparkler" or a "Diamond Martini."\n* **Edible glitter:** Add edible glitter to the food and drinks to give them an extra touch of sparkle.\n\n**Activities:**\n\n* **Jewelry scavenger hunt:** Hide small pieces of jewelry or jewelry-related items around the party area and give clues for guests to find them.\n* **Jewelry-making contest:** Host a contest where guests can show off their jewelry-making skills. You could have a panel of judges or let the guests vote on their favorite piece.\n* **Jewelry-themed games:** Play games that involve jewelry, such as "Pin the Diamond on the Necklace" or "Jewelry Bingo."\n\n**Favors:**\n\n* **Small jewelry pieces:** Give each guest a small piece of jewelry, such as a silver earring or a diamond-shaped charm, as a party favor.\n* **Jewelry-making kits:** Provide each guest with a jewelry-making kit, complete with beads, strings, and other materials, so they can continue creating their own jewelry at home.\n\nI hope these ideas help you plan a sparkling and memorable party for your sister!', "A GPS logger and OBD-II reader can be an incredibly valuable tool for tracking your car's performance data and improving your driving skills. Here are some recommendations:\n\n**GPS Logger:**\n\n1. **Garmin VIRB Ultra 30**: A high-end GPS logger that provides accurate speed, distance, and lap time data. It's waterproof, has a long battery life, and can connect to your smartphone via Bluetooth.\n2. **Racelogic VBOX Sport**: A GPS logger specifically designed for motorsports and performance driving. It's highly accurate, has a compact design, and can provide detailed data on speed, acceleration, and braking.\n3. **AIM Solo 2**: A popular GPS logger among track enthusiasts, offering high-accuracy data on speed, distance, and lap times. It's also compact, waterproof, and has a long battery life.\n\n**OBD-II Reader:**\n\n1. **PLX Kiwi 3**: A high-end OBD-II reader that provides real-time data on engine performance, including RPM, throttle position, and fuel injection. It's compatible with most vehicles and has a user-friendly app.\n2. **OBDLink MX+:** A highly-regarded OBD-II reader that offers advanced features like real-time data streaming, fuel economy tracking, and customizable alerts. It's also compatible with a wide range of vehicles.\n3. **ScanTool 427201 OBDLink LX**: A budget-friendly OBD-II reader that still provides a wealth of data, including engine performance, fuel economy, and trouble codes. It's compatible with most vehicles and has a user-friendly app.\n\n**Combination Devices:**\n\n1. **Harry's Lap Timer**: A GPS logger and OBD-II reader combo device that provides detailed data on speed, distance, and lap times, as well as engine performance data. It's a great option for those who want an all-in-one solution.\n2. **RaceChrono**: A GPS logger and OBD-II reader combo device that offers advanced features like predictive lap timing, throttle and brake analysis, and customizable data overlays. It's a popular choice among track enthusiasts.\n\nWhen choosing a GPS logger and OBD-II reader, consider the following factors:\n\n* **Accuracy**: Look for devices with high accuracy ratings and reviews from other users.\n* **Compatibility**: Ensure the device is compatible with your vehicle's make and model.\n* **Ease of use**: Choose a device with a user-friendly interface and app, especially if you're new to data analysis.\n* **Features**: Consider the types of data you want to track and the features that are important to you (e.g., lap timing, engine performance, fuel economy).\n* **Price**: GPS loggers and OBD-II readers can range from affordable to very expensive, so set a budget and choose a device that meets your needs within that range.\n\nRemember to always follow the manufacturer's instructions for installation and use, and ensure you're using the device safely and responsibly on the track or road.", "I'd be happy to help you organize your sources by theme or category. Here's a suggested grouping of your sources:\n\n**Language Acquisition Theories**\n\n* Hirsch, J. H. (2009). Theories of language acquisition.\n* Duff, P. A. (2015). Language acquisition and development: An introduction.\n\nThese two sources provide a foundation for understanding language acquisition theories, including cognitive, social, and emotional factors that influence language development.\n\n**Instructional Design**\n\n* Tennyson, R. D. (2010). Instructional design: The ADDIE approach.\n* Graves, K. (2017). Designing language courses: A guide for teachers.\n\nThese two sources focus on instructional design principles and their application to language teaching and learning. Tennyson's book provides an overview of the ADDIE model, while Graves' book offers practical guidance on designing language courses.\n\n**Empirical Research**\n\n* Chang, H.-Y., & Chen, Y.-C. (2018). The effect of instructional design on language learning outcomes: A meta-analysis.\n* Shehadeh, A., & Tardy, C. M. (2016). The role of task-based instruction in language acquisition: A systematic review.\n* Warschauer, M., & Cotten, S. R. (2017). Computer-assisted language learning: A review of the literature.\n\nThese three sources present empirical research on the effectiveness of instructional design, task-based instruction, and technology-enhanced language learning. They provide evidence-based findings and recommendations for language teaching and learning.\n\n**Cognitive Load Management**\n\n* Singh, P., & Sharma, S. K. (2020). Cognitive load management in language instruction: A review of the literature.\n\nThis source focuses specifically on cognitive load management in language instruction, providing recommendations for optimizing cognitive load to enhance language learning.\n\n**Technology-Enhanced Language Learning**\n\n* Warschauer, M., & Cotten, S. R. (2017). Computer-assisted language learning: A review of the literature.\n* ReCALL (Journal): Various articles on technology-enhanced language instruction.\n* International Journal of Instructional Technology and Distance Learning (Journal): Various articles on technology-enhanced language instruction.\n\nThese sources explore the role of technology in language learning, including the effectiveness of computer-assisted language learning, online language instruction, and technology-enhanced language teaching.\n\n**General Language Teaching and Learning**\n\n* The Modern Language Journal (Journal): Various articles on language teaching and learning.\n* Instructional Science (Journal): Various articles on instructional design and language acquisition.\n* The Language Learning Journal (Journal): Various articles on language acquisition and teaching.\n\nThese journals cover a range of topics related to language teaching and learning, including instructional design, language acquisition, and technology-enhanced language instruction.\n\nBy grouping your sources into these categories, you can focus on specific themes and areas of interest, making it easier to review and synthesize the information."]

