["Prices can be a crucial factor in our art supply shopping decisions. Jerry's Artarama is generally known for offering competitive prices on art supplies, including cold press watercolor papers. Here's a rough idea of what you can expect:\n\n**Price Range:**\n\nCold press watercolor papers at Jerry's Artarama typically fall within the following price ranges:\n\n* Sheets (20x30 inches):\n\t+ Student-grade: $5-$10 per sheet\n\t+ Mid-range: $10-$20 per sheet\n\t+ Professional-grade: $20-$30 per sheet\n* Blocks (9x12 inches):\n\t+ Student-grade: $10-$20 per block\n\t+ Mid-range: $20-$40 per block\n\t+ Professional-grade: $40-$60 per block\n* Rolls (20 yards):\n\t+ Student-grade: $20-$40 per roll\n\t+ Mid-range: $40-$60 per roll\n\t+ Professional-grade: $60-$80 per roll\n\n**Comparison to Other Art Supply Stores:**\n\nJerry's Artarama's prices for cold press watercolor papers are generally competitive with other art supply stores in the NYC area. Here's a rough comparison:\n\n* Dick Blick Art Materials: Prices are similar to Jerry's Artarama, with some papers potentially being a few dollars more or less.\n* New York Central Art Supply: Prices might be slightly higher than Jerry's Artarama, especially for professional-grade papers.\n* Online Retailers (e.g., Amazon, Cheap Joe's): Online prices can be lower, especially for bulk purchases or student-grade papers. However, be aware that shipping costs and potential quality differences might affect the overall value.\n\n**Tips for Saving Money:**\n\n1. **Buy in bulk:** Purchasing larger quantities of paper or blocks can lead to cost savings.\n2. **Student-grade options:** If you're a beginner or on a tight budget, consider student-grade papers, which are often more affordable.\n3. **Sales and discounts:** Keep an eye on Jerry's Artarama's website, social media, and email newsletters for promotions, sales, and discounts.\n4. **Loyalty program:** Jerry's Artarama has a loyalty program that can help you earn points and rewards, which can be redeemed for discounts or free merchandise.\n5. **Consider alternative brands:** If you're not particular about a specific brand, look for more affordable options from other manufacturers.\n\nKeep in mind that prices may vary depending on the specific product, location, and availability. It's always a good idea to check prices online or in-store before making a purchase.", '30309 is in Atlanta, GA.\n\nFor native plant nurseries in your area, here are a few options:\n\n1. **Piedmont Nurseries**: They have a wide selection of native plants, and their website allows you to filter by "Native" under the "Plant Finder" section. (About 10 miles from 30309)\n2. **Native Gardens**: As their name suggests, they specialize in native plants and offer a variety of species. They also have a online catalog and offer delivery or pickup options. (About 15 miles from 30309)\n3. **Cumberland Nurseries**: They have a native plant section on their website, and they offer online shopping with in-store pickup or delivery options. (About 20 miles from 30309)\n4. **Georgia Native Plant Society**: While not a nursery, the Georgia Native Plant Society is a great resource for finding native plants and connecting with local experts. They often have plant sales and events.\n\nFor online retailers selling organic gardening supplies, here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Gardener\'s Supply Company**: They offer a wide range of organic gardening products, including compost, fertilizers, and pest control methods.\n2. **Burpee**: While they\'re well-known for their seeds, Burpee also offers a selection of organic gardening supplies, including compost and fertilizers.\n3. **Amazon**: Amazon offers a wide selection of organic gardening products from various brands, often with fast shipping and competitive pricing. Be sure to read reviews and check the ingredients and certifications (e.g., OMRI-listed) to ensure you\'re getting a high-quality, organic product.\n4. **E.B. Stone Organics**: This company specializes in organic gardening products, including compost, fertilizers, and soil amendments. They offer online shopping and shipping to Georgia.\n5. **Seeds of Change**: While primarily a seed company, Seeds of Change also offers a selection of organic gardening supplies, including compost and fertilizers.\n\nRemember to always read reviews, check the ingredients, and look for certifications like OMRI (Organic Materials Review Institute) or USDA Organic to ensure you\'re getting a high-quality, organic product.\n\nI hope this helps you find the native plants and organic gardening supplies you need for your garden!', "You're welcome! I'm thrilled to have been able to help. It's always exciting to discover new musicals and connect with others who share similar tastes. I think you'll really enjoy The Perks of Being a Wallflower and Be More Chill - they're both fantastic shows that deal with relatable themes and feature catchy, memorable music.\n\nRemember, musical theater is all about community and sharing the love, so don't hesitate to reach out if you need more recommendations or just want to geek out about your favorite shows. I'm always here to chat and help.\n\nBreak a leg with your guitar playing, and I hope you have a blast exploring these new musicals!"]

