["Choosing the right closet system can be overwhelming, but with customization options, you can find a solution that fits your closet's unique dimensions and your personal style. Here are some popular closet system brands and websites that offer customization options:\n\n**1. The Container Store**\n\n* Website: [www.containerstore.com](http://www.containerstore.com)\n* Customization options: Their closet design team will work with you to create a custom design based on your closet's dimensions and needs.\n* Products: Elfa, Avera, and custom solutions\n\n**2. California Closets**\n\n* Website: [www.californiaclosets.com](http://www.californiaclosets.com)\n* Customization options: In-home consultations and 3D design software to create a custom design tailored to your space and style.\n* Products: Custom closet systems, shelving, and accessories\n\n**3. ClosetMaid**\n\n* Website: [www.closetmaid.com](http://www.closetmaid.com)\n* Customization options: Online design tool and in-store consultations to create a custom design.\n* Products: ShelfTrack, Shelf Liner, and Custom Closet Systems\n\n**4. IKEA**\n\n* Website: [www.ikea.com](http://www.ikea.com)\n* Customization options: Online planning tools and in-store consultations to design a custom closet system using their ALGOT and KOMPLEMENT products.\n* Products: ALGOT, KOMPLEMENT, and PAX closet systems\n\n**5. Home Depot**\n\n* Website: [www.homedepot.com](http://www.homedepot.com)\n* Customization options: Online design tool and in-store consultations to create a custom design using their Martha Stewart Living and ClosetMaid products.\n* Products: Martha Stewart Living and ClosetMaid closet systems\n\n**6. Lowe's**\n\n* Website: [www.lowes.com](http://www.lowes.com)\n* Customization options: Online design tool and in-store consultations to create a custom design using their Allen + Roth and ClosetMaid products.\n* Products: Allen + Roth and ClosetMaid closet systems\n\n**7. Organized Living**\n\n* Website: [www.organizedliving.com](http://www.organizedliving.com)\n* Customization options: Online design tool and in-store consultations to create a custom design using their freedomRail and freedomWall products.\n* Products: freedomRail, freedomWall, and custom closet systems\n\n**8. Rubbermaid**\n\n* Website: [www.rubbermaid.com](http://www.rubbermaid.com)\n* Customization options: Online design tool and in-store consultations to create a custom design using their Configurations and FastTrack products.\n* Products: Configurations, FastTrack, and closet organization systems\n\nThese are just a few popular options, and there are many more brands and websites available. Before choosing a brand, consider the following factors:\n\n1. Budget: Set a budget and look for brands that offer solutions within your price range.\n2. Style: Choose a brand that offers products that fit your personal style and decor.\n3. Customization options: Consider brands that offer online design tools, in-store consultations, or both.\n4. Quality: Research the brand's reputation, product quality, and warranty offered.\n5. Installation: Check if the brand offers installation services or DIY options.\n\nOnce you've narrowed down your options, you can schedule a consultation or start designing your custom closet system online. Happy designing!", "Facial steamers can be a great addition to your skincare routine! Steaming can help loosen dirt, unclog pores, and prepare your skin for exfoliation. Here's what you need to know:\n\n**Benefits of facial steamers:**\n\n1. **Deep cleansing**: Steam helps to open up pores, allowing for a deeper cleanse and removal of dirt, oil, and impurities.\n2. **Improved exfoliation**: Steaming can make exfoliation more effective by loosening dead skin cells and debris, making it easier to remove them.\n3. **Hydration**: Steam can help to hydrate the skin, leaving it feeling softer and more supple.\n4. **Reduced pores**: Regular steaming can help to reduce the appearance of pores over time.\n\n**Features to look for in a facial steamer:**\n\n1. **Adjustable steam settings**: Look for a steamer with adjustable steam settings to control the intensity and temperature of the steam.\n2. **Multiple steam modes**: Some steamers come with different steam modes, such as a gentle mist or a more intense steam. This can be beneficial for different skin types and concerns.\n3. **Cool mist function**: A cool mist function can help to close pores and reduce puffiness after steaming.\n4. **Ionic technology**: Some steamers incorporate ionic technology, which can help to purify the steam and reduce bacteria.\n5. **Easy to clean**: Look for a steamer with a removable and easy-to-clean facial plate to prevent bacterial buildup.\n6. **Compact design**: Consider a compact, travel-friendly design if you plan to use the steamer at home and on-the-go.\n7. **Affordability**: Facial steamers can range from under $20 to over $100, so set a budget and look for a steamer that meets your needs within that range.\n\n**Tips for using a facial steamer:**\n\n1. **Use distilled water**: Use distilled water to prevent mineral buildup and bacterial growth.\n2. **Steam for 5-10 minutes**: Steam your face for 5-10 minutes to allow your pores to open up and your skin to benefit from the steam.\n3. **Be gentle**: Be gentle when steaming, especially around the delicate skin around your eyes and mouth.\n4. **Follow up with toner and moisturizer**: After steaming, follow up with a toner and moisturizer to help balance your skin's pH and lock in hydration.\n\nRemember to always read reviews and do your research before purchasing a facial steamer to find the best one for your skin type and concerns.", 'With a budget of $800 to $1,200, you can build a solid desktop that can handle your internet connection and more.\n\n**CPU (Central Processing Unit):**\n\nFor a smooth internet experience, a mid-range CPU from Intel Core i5 or AMD Ryzen 5 series should be sufficient. These CPUs offer a good balance of performance and power efficiency.\n\n* Intel Core i5-11400F: A great option for general use and internet browsing. ($179)\n* AMD Ryzen 5 5600X: Offers excellent performance and multitasking capabilities. ($329)\n\n**Motherboard:**\n\nA motherboard with a good chipset and features like Wi-Fi, USB 3.2 Gen 2, and SATA 6Gb/s will ensure a smooth internet experience.\n\n* ASRock B450M Steel Legend Micro ATX AM4 Motherboard: A solid option with Wi-Fi, USB 3.2 Gen 2, and SATA 6Gb/s. ($129)\n* MSI B550M BAZOOKA Motherboard: Offers Wi-Fi, USB 3.2 Gen 2, SATA 6Gb/s, and high-quality audio. ($199)\n\n**RAM (Memory):**\n\n16GB of RAM is a good starting point for general use and internet browsing. You can always add more later if needed.\n\n* Corsair Vengeance LPX 16GB (2x8GB) DDR4 RAM: A popular and reliable option. ($69)\n\n**Storage:**\n\nA fast SSD (Solid-State Drive) will greatly improve your desktop\'s overall performance and internet experience.\n\n* Western Digital Black SN750 512GB NVMe SSD: A fast and reliable SSD for storing your OS and programs. ($129)\n* Seagate BarraCuda 1TB 3.5" HDD: A spacious HDD for storage. ($59)\n\n**Wi-Fi Adapter:**\n\nSince you mentioned you want to take advantage of your mesh network system, a good Wi-Fi adapter is essential.\n\n* Intel Wi-Fi 6 (Gig+) Desktop Kit: Offers Wi-Fi 6 connectivity and Bluetooth 5.0. ($25)\n\n**Power Supply:**\n\nA 300-350W power supply should be sufficient for your build.\n\n* EVGA 300 GS, 80+ Gold 300W: A reliable and efficient power supply. ($35)\n\n**Case:**\n\nA well-ventilated case with good cable management options will keep your desktop running smoothly and looking tidy.\n\n* Fractal Design Meshify C ATX Mid Tower Case: A popular case with excellent airflow and cable management. ($59)\n\nHere\'s a sample build that should fit your budget and meet your requirements:\n\n* CPU: Intel Core i5-11400F\n* Motherboard: ASRock B450M Steel Legend Micro ATX AM4 Motherboard\n* RAM: Corsair Vengeance LPX 16GB (2x8GB) DDR4 RAM\n* Storage: Western Digital Black SN750 512GB NVMe SSD + Seagate BarraCuda 1TB 3.5" HDD\n* Wi-Fi Adapter: Intel Wi-Fi 6 (Gig+) Desktop Kit\n* Power Supply: EVGA 300 GS, 80+ Gold 300W\n* Case: Fractal Design Meshify C ATX Mid Tower Case\n\nThis build should provide a smooth internet experience, and you can always upgrade individual components later as needed.\n\nHow does this build look to you? Would you like to make any changes or additions?']

